378
00:32:03,104 --> 00:32:07,215
<b>(Tonight, I want to take you to the cottage...)</b>

379
00:32:41,076 --> 00:32:42,615
<b>Hae Won.</b>

380
00:32:53,855 --> 00:32:55,265
<b>Hae Won?</b>

381
00:33:00,295 --> 00:33:03,435
<b>Hae Won. What are you...</b>

382
00:33:05,467 --> 00:33:06,675
<b>Hey!</b>

383
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:10,915
<b>Irene was me?</b>

384
00:33:13,341 --> 00:33:14,745
<b>You said it was Hwi.</b>

385
00:33:16,578 --> 00:33:19,025
<b>Then was that key chain really from me?</b>

386
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,685
<b>No. How...</b>

387
00:33:21,216 --> 00:33:22,710
<b>How much did you read?</b>

388
00:33:22,717 --> 00:33:24,450
<b>Then what does "Good night, Irene" mean?</b>

389
00:33:24,452 --> 00:33:25,520
<b>No.</b>

390
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:28,350
<b>That's just from some lyrics of a song that I like.</b>

391
00:33:28,356 --> 00:33:30,150
<b>- Why am I Irene? - That's because...</b>

392
00:33:30,158 --> 00:33:31,450
<b>you gave me that key chain.</b>

393
00:33:31,459 --> 00:33:33,465
<b>But you said you made it.</b>

394
00:33:40,935 --> 00:33:44,775
<b>I didn't know you kept a diary, Eun Seop. How cute.</b>

395
00:33:46,041 --> 00:33:49,085
<b>Can you tell me how much you read?</b>

396
00:33:50,545 --> 00:33:51,715
<b>I'm not sure.</b>

397
00:33:52,047 --> 00:33:55,455
<b>So you were the one who gave me that bug when we were young.</b>

398
00:34:01,356 --> 00:34:04,190
<b>- I don't want this. - What?</b>

399
00:34:04,192 --> 00:34:06,205
<b>I don't want this. Take it back. Now.</b>

400
00:34:09,864 --> 00:34:12,000
<b>That's because I thought you were a boy.</b>

401
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:14,860
<b>What? Why? Why did you think I was a boy?</b>

402
00:34:14,869 --> 00:34:17,400
<b>Because you were covering your face with a hat.</b>

403
00:34:17,405 --> 00:34:20,445
<b>What? Goodness. This is unbelievable.</b>

404
00:34:20,675 --> 00:34:22,385
<b>Oh, and...</b>

405
00:34:22,777 --> 00:34:25,255
<b>you even slept at my house.</b>

406
00:34:39,294 --> 00:34:40,565
<b>Who...</b>

407
00:34:41,229 --> 00:34:42,875
<b>are you?</b>

408
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:46,705
<b>That's because Hwi suddenly got sick.</b>

409
00:34:47,368 --> 00:34:49,870
<b>My parents took her to a hospital in Seoul so I had to sleep over.</b>

410
00:34:49,871 --> 00:34:54,045
<b>So that's why you fell in love again with a fairy like me.</b>

411
00:34:54,476 --> 00:34:56,155
<b>This is so fun, Eun Seop.</b>

412
00:34:59,581 --> 00:35:01,740
<b>- Did you read all of it? - Of course not.</b>

413
00:35:01,749 --> 00:35:03,325
<b>Almost all of it.</b>

414
00:35:06,054 --> 00:35:09,090
<b>Now I finally know the secret of the Nakdong River incident.</b>

415
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:11,895
<b>I was baffled by the timing my aunt came for me.</b>

416
00:35:12,026 --> 00:35:13,935
<b>You were the one who called her.</b>

417
00:35:15,797 --> 00:35:19,105
<b>I didn't even know that and almost believed in fate.</b>

418
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:20,375
<b>Gosh.</b>

419
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:25,340
<b>It's all right, Eun Seop. I won't tease you.</b>

420
00:35:25,340 --> 00:35:28,085
<b>My lips are sealed. Come on, don't be so sad.</b>

421
00:35:28,409 --> 00:35:30,140
<b>- I'm ruined. - Eun Seop.</b>

422
00:35:30,145 --> 00:35:31,285
<b>What?</b>

423
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,240
<b>- "That day, Irene asked." - Stop.</b>

424
00:35:34,249 --> 00:35:35,750
<b>- "Over there." - I said, stop.</b>

425
00:35:35,750 --> 00:35:37,350
<b>"Those things that look like marshmallows."</b>

426
00:35:37,352 --> 00:35:40,565
<b>- Be quiet! No, Stop! - "What are they called?"</b>

427
00:35:43,525 --> 00:35:44,695
<b>Wait.</b>

428
00:35:45,059 --> 00:35:47,105
<b>Yes, this is Good Night Bookstore.</b>

429
00:35:47,695 --> 00:35:48,875
<b>What?</b>

430
00:35:55,670 --> 00:35:58,870
<b>(Hyecheon Station)</b>

431
00:35:58,873 --> 00:36:00,845
<b>What are you doing here again?</b>

432
00:36:01,709 --> 00:36:03,915
<b>You told me about the train schedule.</b>

433
00:36:04,479 --> 00:36:05,725
<b>Yun Taek.</b>

434
00:36:07,048 --> 00:36:09,195
<b>I lost hope.</b>

435
00:36:09,517 --> 00:36:11,295
<b>I have nothing left now.</b>

436
00:36:11,819 --> 00:36:15,295
<b>So don't expect anything from me.</b>

437
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:17,565
<b>Shim Myeong Yeo.</b>

438
00:36:21,963 --> 00:36:24,005
<b>Your hair...</b>

439
00:36:24,866 --> 00:36:28,915
<b>smelled like the "Charming" shampoo my mom used to use.</b>

440
00:36:48,089 --> 00:36:49,835
<b>And your eyes...</b>

441
00:36:50,692 --> 00:36:54,105
<b>reminded me of the night before a rainstorm.</b>

442
00:36:57,832 --> 00:36:59,675
<b>I really loved that about you.</b>

443
00:37:04,205 --> 00:37:05,445
<b>Can you tell me?</b>

444
00:37:07,041 --> 00:37:09,715
<b>That none of it is true?</b>

445
00:37:12,580 --> 00:37:13,880
<b>What's not true?</b>

446
00:37:13,881 --> 00:37:15,155
<b>Everything.</b>

447
00:37:15,383 --> 00:37:17,680
<b>Oh, the rumor that my sister killed her husband...</b>

448
00:37:17,685 --> 00:37:20,095
<b>because he had an affair with me?</b>

449
00:37:21,789 --> 00:37:22,935
<b>Well...</b>

450
00:37:23,591 --> 00:37:25,435
<b>People can believe what they want to believe.</b>

451
00:37:26,027 --> 00:37:28,205
<b>The outcome won't change regardless of what you believe.</b>

452
00:37:28,496 --> 00:37:30,690
<b>Whether I had an affair with my brother-in-law or not,</b>

453
00:37:30,698 --> 00:37:32,575
<b>he died, and that won't change.</b>

454
00:37:33,167 --> 00:37:35,675
<b>And whether my sister killed him or not,</b>

455
00:37:36,804 --> 00:37:38,745
<b>she went to jail.</b>

456
00:37:39,107 --> 00:37:41,415
<b>And even if she didn't go to jail,</b>

457
00:37:41,843 --> 00:37:43,915
<b>I'd still be the mess that I am today.</b>

458
00:37:45,413 --> 00:37:48,140
<b>So it doesn't matter. Whatever you believe is the truth.</b>

459
00:37:48,149 --> 00:37:49,755
<b>- No. - Yes.</b>

460
00:37:50,785 --> 00:37:52,395
<b>That is the truth,</b>

461
00:37:52,787 --> 00:37:54,025
<b>Cha Yun Taek.</b>

462
00:38:00,428 --> 00:38:04,775
<b>(Hyecheon Station)</b>

463
00:38:04,999 --> 00:38:07,045
<b>Even if that is the truth,</b>

464
00:38:07,368 --> 00:38:11,315
<b>you should tell me that it isn't.</b>

465
00:38:12,407 --> 00:38:14,985
<b>That's the least you can do for me. Am I wrong?</b>

466
00:38:18,479 --> 00:38:19,625
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

467
00:38:21,249 --> 00:38:22,895
<b>I'm inconsiderate, you know.</b>

468
00:38:25,253 --> 00:38:26,625
<b>Myeong Yeo.</b>

469
00:38:28,289 --> 00:38:29,495
<b>I...</b>

470
00:38:33,661 --> 00:38:34,865
<b>I have...</b>

471
00:38:37,465 --> 00:38:39,075
<b>wilted.</b>

472
00:38:39,467 --> 00:38:41,775
<b>We all have.</b>

473
00:38:42,937 --> 00:38:45,275
<b>I've wilted as much as you have.</b>

474
00:38:57,018 --> 00:38:58,225
<b>Come on.</b>

475
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:01,065
<b>I'm the only one who has completely wilted.</b>

476
00:39:02,290 --> 00:39:03,535
<b>I'm the only one...</b>

477
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:08,205
<b>who's totally dead, Yun Taek.</b>

478
00:39:26,814 --> 00:39:28,910
<b>"I will cut off the tips of my five fingers..."</b>

479
00:39:28,916 --> 00:39:30,795
<b>"and draw a staff with my blood."</b>

480
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,050
<b>"I will be alone tonight, but I won't be lonely."</b>

481
00:39:33,054 --> 00:39:34,365
<b>"And tonight, I will shed tears."</b>

482
00:39:37,692 --> 00:39:41,005
<b>"The first glass is for you, who left me."</b>

483
00:39:44,265 --> 00:39:48,645
<b>"The second glass is for me, who is already so pathetic."</b>

484
00:39:52,073 --> 00:39:56,085
<b>"Another glass for our eternal love."</b>

485
00:39:59,046 --> 00:40:00,185
<b>"And..."</b>

486
00:40:01,182 --> 00:40:04,925
<b>"the last glass is for the Almighty who foresaw..."</b>

487
00:40:05,086 --> 00:40:06,695
<b>"and decided everything in advance."</b>

488
00:40:07,722 --> 00:40:10,995
<b>(Good Night Bookstore)</b>

489
00:40:11,893 --> 00:40:13,790
<b>Hello, I'm Ji Eun Sil.</b>

490
00:40:13,795 --> 00:40:15,360
<b>I work at Gangneung City Hall.</b>

491
00:40:15,363 --> 00:40:16,960
<b>I'm taking some time off work...</b>

492
00:40:16,964 --> 00:40:17,990
<b>because of the event.</b>

493
00:40:17,999 --> 00:40:19,660
<b>That's why I'm here today.</b>

494
00:40:19,667 --> 00:40:20,805
<b>Applause!</b>

495
00:40:23,871 --> 00:40:25,970
<b>My gosh, a number of new members...</b>

496
00:40:25,973 --> 00:40:28,340
<b>have joined us recently.</b>

497
00:40:28,342 --> 00:40:29,540
<b>It's encouraging.</b>

498
00:40:29,544 --> 00:40:32,680
<b>Jang Woo, you look a little spaced out today.</b>

499
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:34,925
<b>Me? No, I'm not.</b>

500
00:40:34,982 --> 00:40:36,480
<b>- Jang Woo. - Yes.</b>

501
00:40:36,484 --> 00:40:38,450
<b>Did you drink something hot?</b>

502
00:40:38,453 --> 00:40:41,525
<b>No, I only drink iced Americano.</b>

503
00:41:01,542 --> 00:41:03,770
<b>"When I realized I hadn't had a chance to tell you..."</b>

504
00:41:03,778 --> 00:41:06,810
<b>"that I loved you with all my heart,"</b>

505
00:41:06,814 --> 00:41:09,855
<b>"you were already in love with someone else."</b>

506
00:41:10,184 --> 00:41:13,020
<b>"I silenced the passionate serenade inside my heart..."</b>

507
00:41:13,020 --> 00:41:15,965
<b>"as you drifted far away from me."</b>

508
00:41:16,224 --> 00:41:19,190
<b>"You told me to forget everything..."</b>

509
00:41:19,193 --> 00:41:22,375
<b>"before your pretty smile vanished and only remember your beauty,"</b>

510
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:23,990
<b>"but to a man,"</b>

511
00:41:23,998 --> 00:41:26,545
<b>"a woman either signifies joy or sorrow."</b>

512
00:41:27,368 --> 00:41:29,515
<b>"Love" by Cho Chi Hun.</b>

513
00:41:30,805 --> 00:41:32,175
<b>What's that?</b>

514
00:41:32,306 --> 00:41:34,345
<b>It's a poem.</b>

515
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:39,025
<b>It makes my heart ache every time I hear it.</b>

516
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:41,555
<b>Why does your heart ache, Auntie?</b>

517
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:44,595
<b>Is love painful?</b>

518
00:41:44,986 --> 00:41:46,325
<b>Well...</b>

519
00:41:46,754 --> 00:41:49,495
<b>For me, no. But I'm not sure.</b>

520
00:41:50,558 --> 00:41:54,605
<b>Jang Woo, is love painful for you?</b>

521
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:01,675
<b>Did your crush who rejected you...</b>

522
00:42:01,969 --> 00:42:03,215
<b>break your heart?</b>

523
00:42:04,138 --> 00:42:05,200
<b>Eun Seop, get me some tissue.</b>

524
00:42:05,206 --> 00:42:07,085
<b>I'll bring it.</b>

525
00:42:08,075 --> 00:42:09,215
<b>What's wrong?</b>

526
00:42:09,510 --> 00:42:11,185
<b>- Hae Won went to grab it? - Yes.</b>

527
00:42:29,564 --> 00:42:30,705
<b>(Bookstore Diary)</b>

528
00:42:35,870 --> 00:42:37,145
<b>(The 130th Story)</b>

529
00:42:37,471 --> 00:42:39,000
<b>(The Bookstore in the Ocean)</b>

530
00:42:39,006 --> 00:42:41,915
<b>(Hae Won, I understand that you will leave this place one day.)</b>

531
00:42:42,944 --> 00:42:44,085
<b>Hae Won.</b>

532
00:42:45,179 --> 00:42:46,585
<b>I understand...</b>

533
00:42:47,315 --> 00:42:49,825
<b>that you will leave this place one day.</b>

534
00:42:55,523 --> 00:42:56,665
<b>Hae Won.</b>

535
00:42:57,258 --> 00:42:59,535
<b>- Yes. - Hae Won, someone's on the phone.</b>

536
00:42:59,927 --> 00:43:01,065
<b>Who?</b>

537
00:43:01,128 --> 00:43:02,975
<b>She said her name is Bo Yeong.</b>

538
00:43:05,566 --> 00:43:06,705
<b>Oh, okay.</b>

539
00:43:09,270 --> 00:43:10,415
<b>Well...</b>

540
00:43:10,871 --> 00:43:12,870
<b>I think Jang Woo was probably...</b>

541
00:43:12,873 --> 00:43:14,270
<b>No, no way.</b>

542
00:43:14,275 --> 00:43:16,870
<b>No, I've never been heartbroken because of love.</b>

543
00:43:16,877 --> 00:43:18,810
<b>I swear...</b>

544
00:43:18,813 --> 00:43:21,655
<b>on the rice field road where I walk every single day.</b>

545
00:43:22,049 --> 00:43:24,410
<b>But one-sided love is sad.</b>

546
00:43:24,418 --> 00:43:26,520
<b>- Hey. - That's what I learned from books.</b>

547
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:28,250
<b>- Hey. - Seung Ho.</b>

548
00:43:28,255 --> 00:43:29,650
<b>You know so many things.</b>

549
00:43:29,657 --> 00:43:31,690
<b>Seung Ho, do you have a girlfriend?</b>

550
00:43:31,692 --> 00:43:32,820
<b>No, I don't.</b>

551
00:43:32,827 --> 00:43:34,090
<b>The other day, you said you did.</b>

552
00:43:34,095 --> 00:43:36,330
<b>- No, that's not true. I didn't. - My gosh!</b>

553
00:43:36,330 --> 00:43:38,030
<b>- Who's this girl? - I don't have a girlfriend.</b>

554
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:40,860
<b>- Your face is turning red. - I don't have one.</b>

555
00:43:40,868 --> 00:43:42,305
<b>I don't have a girlfriend.</b>

556
00:43:42,503 --> 00:43:44,175
<b>No, it's not true.</b>

557
00:43:44,572 --> 00:43:46,615
<b>- Why is your face beet red? - It's not.</b>

558
00:44:13,801 --> 00:44:15,205
<b>Giddy up! Let's go!</b>

559
00:44:20,241 --> 00:44:21,945
<b>Faster!</b>

560
00:44:22,009 --> 00:44:23,615
<b>Giddy up! Let's go!</b>

561
00:44:46,734 --> 00:44:48,605
<b>Out of the way!</b>

562
00:44:49,403 --> 00:44:50,800
<b>Hi!</b>

563
00:44:50,805 --> 00:44:52,885
<b>(Hyecheon High School)</b>

564
00:44:53,674 --> 00:44:55,445
<b>Hi!</b>

565
00:44:55,643 --> 00:44:57,255
<b>Oh, it's Hwi.</b>

566
00:44:57,445 --> 00:44:59,285
<b>Hi!</b>

567
00:45:01,015 --> 00:45:02,225
<b>Good morning, sir!</b>

568
00:45:14,028 --> 00:45:17,175
<b>What a beautiful morning.</b>

569
00:45:19,033 --> 00:45:24,100
<b>(Bukhyeon Three-way Intersection)</b>

570
00:45:24,105 --> 00:45:26,785
<b>(Bukhyeon-ri, Downtown Hyecheon, Seohyeon Village)</b>

571
00:45:50,264 --> 00:45:53,205
<b>I've never had anyone asking to meet up on the bus.</b>

572
00:45:56,871 --> 00:45:58,345
<b>What did you want to talk to me about?</b>

573
00:46:01,342 --> 00:46:03,915
<b>I thought about what you said.</b>

574
00:46:07,815 --> 00:46:10,795
<b>About how twisted I am.</b>

575
00:46:13,888 --> 00:46:17,035
<b>You're right. I was like that.</b>

576
00:46:18,292 --> 00:46:20,665
<b>I really hated you.</b>

577
00:46:22,196 --> 00:46:23,505
<b>I mean, think about it.</b>

578
00:46:24,165 --> 00:46:27,005
<b>You cut all ties with me after just one strike.</b>

579
00:46:27,434 --> 00:46:29,175
<b>Because of one mistake.</b>

580
00:46:29,236 --> 00:46:31,345
<b>You didn't even want to listen to me.</b>

581
00:46:32,373 --> 00:46:34,900
<b>Hae Won, just a moment.</b>

582
00:46:34,909 --> 00:46:36,115
<b>Let go!</b>

583
00:46:37,578 --> 00:46:40,425
<b>Hae Won!</b>

584
00:46:47,121 --> 00:46:49,835
<b>No matter how hard I tried,</b>

585
00:46:50,124 --> 00:46:52,465
<b>you wouldn't even look at me.</b>

586
00:46:53,627 --> 00:46:57,490
<b>When I heard you were here, I went to see you.</b>

587
00:46:57,498 --> 00:46:58,805
<b>So?</b>

588
00:47:00,768 --> 00:47:04,115
<b>Are you saying you still can't forgive me?</b>

589
00:47:06,307 --> 00:47:09,045
<b>So I started waiting.</b>

590
00:47:10,010 --> 00:47:11,455
<b>Waiting for what?</b>

591
00:47:12,646 --> 00:47:14,410
<b>For your forgiveness...</b>

592
00:47:14,415 --> 00:47:16,895
<b>to become overdue.</b>

593
00:47:17,852 --> 00:47:20,965
<b>Then you'd become a petty and cold person,</b>

594
00:47:21,522 --> 00:47:23,550
<b>and I'd become this miserable person,</b>

595
00:47:23,557 --> 00:47:26,405
<b>who is pitied by everyone.</b>

596
00:47:31,165 --> 00:47:33,075
<b>"One strike"?</b>

597
00:47:34,969 --> 00:47:36,145
<b>Bo Yeong.</b>

598
00:47:36,804 --> 00:47:39,715
<b>It might have been one strike for you,</b>

599
00:47:40,241 --> 00:47:42,315
<b>but for me, it was a strikeout.</b>

600
00:47:42,910 --> 00:47:45,940
<b>I told you the biggest secret of my life,</b>

601
00:47:45,946 --> 00:47:48,325
<b>and you didn't keep it to yourself.</b>

602
00:47:49,683 --> 00:47:52,110
<b>You might try to defend yourself...</b>

603
00:47:52,119 --> 00:47:53,780
<b>by saying you only told Joo Hee,</b>

604
00:47:53,787 --> 00:47:55,420
<b>but because you told that one person...</b>

605
00:47:55,422 --> 00:47:57,765
<b>I didn't think of it like that.</b>

606
00:48:01,862 --> 00:48:03,205
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

607
00:48:09,570 --> 00:48:11,375
<b>But I...</b>

608
00:48:11,772 --> 00:48:15,785
<b>couldn't help thinking it was just one mistake.</b>

609
00:48:17,144 --> 00:48:19,155
<b>So I hated you.</b>

610
00:48:25,019 --> 00:48:28,525
<b>I'm sure you didn't hate me. You just disliked me.</b>

611
00:48:29,223 --> 00:48:31,765
<b>- Are they different? - Yes.</b>

612
00:48:32,192 --> 00:48:33,505
<b>They are.</b>

613
00:48:34,528 --> 00:48:37,605
<b>You can dislike anyone,</b>

614
00:48:38,699 --> 00:48:41,775
<b>but you can only hate someone you like.</b>

615
00:48:45,239 --> 00:48:47,585
<b>I really liked you.</b>

616
00:48:47,741 --> 00:48:50,585
<b>Attention. We have a new transfer student.</b>

617
00:48:52,813 --> 00:48:55,840
<b>Her name is Mok Hae Won. She's from Seoul.</b>

618
00:48:55,849 --> 00:48:59,325
<b>You know the mock exam is next week, right?</b>

619
00:48:59,453 --> 00:49:02,320
<b>- Let's try to score... - She's pretty.</b>

620
00:49:02,323 --> 00:49:05,835
<b>A mill and a guesthouse...</b>

621
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:07,735
<b>are different?</b>

622
00:49:10,030 --> 00:49:11,275
<b>Gosh.</b>

623
00:49:11,765 --> 00:49:15,045
<b>You're very sweet.</b>

624
00:49:16,303 --> 00:49:18,075
<b>That must have been why...</b>

625
00:49:18,172 --> 00:49:20,485
<b>I kept trying so hard and going to see you.</b>

626
00:49:25,980 --> 00:49:30,355
<b>Even if you decided to dislike me...</b>

627
00:49:30,851 --> 00:49:34,025
<b>and never to give me a second chance...</b>

628
00:49:34,955 --> 00:49:37,465
<b>because you only cared about me that much.</b>

629
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:18,530
<b>Hi, I'm Kim Bo Yeong. Nice to meet you.</b>

630
00:50:18,532 --> 00:50:19,845
<b>Hae Won.</b>

631
00:50:21,668 --> 00:50:23,415
<b>Do you want to team up with me?</b>

632
00:50:26,340 --> 00:50:27,785
<b>You can use this.</b>

633
00:50:29,376 --> 00:50:31,915
<b>I live close by, so I can just run home.</b>

634
00:50:33,881 --> 00:50:36,495
<b>Kim Bo Yeong... Bo Yeong.</b>

635
00:50:37,618 --> 00:50:39,795
<b>See you tomorrow, Hae Won!</b>

636
00:50:41,488 --> 00:50:43,165
<b>Bo Yeong!</b>

637
00:50:44,858 --> 00:50:46,035
<b>This...</b>

638
00:50:59,173 --> 00:51:02,245
<b>(Good Night Bookstore)</b>

639
00:51:13,387 --> 00:51:14,725
<b>Hello?</b>

640
00:51:20,494 --> 00:51:23,005
<b>Mr. Jung Gil Bok?</b>

641
00:51:30,737 --> 00:51:32,370
<b>Hello. I'm...</b>

642
00:51:32,372 --> 00:51:34,185
<b>Wait here for a second.</b>

643
00:51:37,211 --> 00:51:39,980
<b>I'm here to see Mr. Jung Gil Bok.</b>

644
00:51:39,980 --> 00:51:42,025
<b>Fill this out, please.</b>

645
00:51:42,382 --> 00:51:45,410
<b>His neighbor found him on the street and brought him here.</b>

646
00:51:45,419 --> 00:51:48,595
<b>It's nothing serious, but he should stay in the hospital for a few days.</b>

647
00:51:48,956 --> 00:51:52,720
<b>But he's insisting on going home.</b>

648
00:51:52,726 --> 00:51:55,565
<b>I think he's worried about the hospital bills.</b>

649
00:52:05,005 --> 00:52:06,245
<b>Seung Ho.</b>

650
00:52:08,809 --> 00:52:10,715
<b>Uncle.</b>

651
00:52:22,222 --> 00:52:23,935
<b>Don't worry too much.</b>

652
00:52:32,699 --> 00:52:34,705
<b>He'll get better soon.</b>

653
00:52:37,204 --> 00:52:39,145
<b>We had...</b>

654
00:52:39,640 --> 00:52:41,445
<b>rabbits at school.</b>

655
00:52:41,642 --> 00:52:44,310
<b>- Run! - Wait for me!</b>

656
00:52:44,311 --> 00:52:46,340
<b>Hey, stop!</b>

657
00:52:46,346 --> 00:52:48,410
<b>Where are you going?</b>

658
00:52:48,415 --> 00:52:49,725
<b>Eat.</b>

659
00:52:50,117 --> 00:52:52,495
<b>They were so cute.</b>

660
00:52:54,955 --> 00:52:56,735
<b>But they died.</b>

661
00:53:00,227 --> 00:53:02,535
<b>What if the same thing happens...</b>

662
00:53:02,863 --> 00:53:05,805
<b>to my grandpa?</b>

663
00:53:10,571 --> 00:53:12,375
<b>He'll be fine.</b>

664
00:53:16,276 --> 00:53:18,115
<b>I promise you.</b>

665
00:53:52,879 --> 00:53:54,085
<b>I'll help you.</b>

666
00:53:56,917 --> 00:53:58,055
<b>There you go.</b>

667
00:54:50,804 --> 00:54:53,285
<b>Yes, you should pat your face.</b>

668
00:54:55,008 --> 00:54:56,215
<b>Under your eyes too.</b>

669
00:55:04,685 --> 00:55:06,925
<b>Pat, pat, pat...</b>

670
00:55:09,222 --> 00:55:11,950
<b>Auntie, can you take out some blankets later?</b>

671
00:55:11,958 --> 00:55:13,360
<b>I will, Ji Yeon,</b>

672
00:55:13,360 --> 00:55:16,105
<b>but I'm not Auntie. I'm Myeong Yeo.</b>

673
00:55:16,697 --> 00:55:18,160
<b>That's right.</b>

674
00:55:18,165 --> 00:55:20,000
<b>Call Myeong Yeo by her first name.</b>

675
00:55:20,000 --> 00:55:22,105
<b>Don't call her Auntie.</b>

676
00:55:22,402 --> 00:55:25,570
<b>Grow up. What's so bad about being called Auntie?</b>

677
00:55:25,572 --> 00:55:27,670
<b>Eun Seop's parents still treat you...</b>

678
00:55:27,674 --> 00:55:29,440
<b>like a high school girl.</b>

679
00:55:29,443 --> 00:55:30,840
<b>You graduated from high school years ago.</b>

680
00:55:30,844 --> 00:55:32,740
<b>That's because I still am like a high school girl.</b>

681
00:55:32,746 --> 00:55:35,910
<b>You do still have a high school girl's skin. What's your secret?</b>

682
00:55:35,916 --> 00:55:38,155
<b>I put something on just now.</b>

683
00:55:39,686 --> 00:55:41,995
<b>Seung Ho, what is that book?</b>

684
00:55:42,155 --> 00:55:43,990
<b>"Owl at Home".</b>

685
00:55:43,990 --> 00:55:45,395
<b>Can I see it too?</b>

686
00:55:45,492 --> 00:55:47,365
<b>Yes, of course.</b>

687
00:55:49,596 --> 00:55:51,960
<b>That's the story about Teardrop Tea.</b>

688
00:55:51,965 --> 00:55:53,030
<b>Yes.</b>

689
00:55:53,033 --> 00:55:57,475
<b>Whenever the owl thinks of something sad and cries,</b>

690
00:55:57,604 --> 00:55:59,330
<b>it gathers its teardrops in a kettle...</b>

691
00:55:59,339 --> 00:56:01,170
<b>and makes Teardrop Tea.</b>

692
00:56:01,174 --> 00:56:04,855
<b>It's a story about how the owl forgets about its sadness like that.</b>

693
00:56:05,412 --> 00:56:07,885
<b>Then shall we make Teardrop Tea too?</b>

694
00:56:08,048 --> 00:56:11,750
